MKTGNI1WA646NWDB.title: Gross National Income for World (DISCONTINUED)
MKTGNI1WA646NWDB.notes:
GNI (formerly GNP) is the sum of value added by all resident producers plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output plus net receipts of primary income (compensation of employees and property income) from abroad. Data are in current U.S. dollars.

Source Code: NY.GNP.MKTP.CD

MKTGNIEZA646NWDB.title: Gross National Income for Euro Area (DISCONTINUED)
MKTGNIEZA646NWDB.notes:
GNI (formerly GNP) is the sum of value added by all resident producers plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output plus net receipts of primary income (compensation of employees and property income) from abroad. Data are in current U.S. dollars.

Source Code: NY.GNP.MKTP.CD

PCAGDP1WA646NWDB.title: Gross Domestic Product Per Capita for World (DISCONTINUED)
PCAGDP1WA646NWDB.notes:
GDP per capita is gross domestic product divided by midyear population. GDP is the sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products. It is calculated without making deductions for depreciation of fabricated assets or for depletion and degradation of natural resources. Data are in current U.S. dollars.

Source Code: NY.GDP.PCAP.CD

PCAGDPEZA646NWDB.title: Gross Domestic Product Per Capita for Euro Area (DISCONTINUED)
PCAGDPEZA646NWDB.notes:
GDP per capita is gross domestic product divided by midyear population. GDP is the sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products. It is calculated without making deductions for depreciation of fabricated assets or for depletion and degradation of natural resources. Data are in current U.S. dollars.

Source Code: NY.GDP.PCAP.CD
